    "Specifically, we compose ATLA with GPTFuzzer (Yu et al., 2023), which learns jailbreaking templates with placeholders to be replaced by harmful questions.",
    "Fuzzer can generate sneaky jailbreaking prompts that evade detectors such as Llama-Guard (Inan et al., 2023).",
    "Our results show that the Metric Question only GPTFuzzer ATLA GPTFuzzer + ATLA ASR 0/50 58/500 397/500 701/5000 FNR 0/50 219/500 12/500 2509/5000",
    "Table 6: We can compose ATLA with a template based method:",
    "We show that the composed methods have the merits from both."
